description: Predict biological response of molecules from their chemical properties. Each instance represents a molecule with calculated molecular descriptors capturing characteristics like size, shape, and elemental constitution.
creator: Boehringer Ingelheim (pharmaceutical company)
feature_description: 1776 molecular descriptors (d1 through d1776) representing calculated properties that capture molecular characteristics including size, shape, elemental constitution, and other chemical properties. All features have been normalized.

target_values.0: Molecule did not elicit biological response

use_case: Drug discovery, virtual screening, molecular activity prediction, chemical compound classification, pharmaceutical research and development
data_collection: Molecular descriptors calculated from chemical structures, with experimental biological activity data
data_characteristics: High-dimensional dataset with normalized molecular descriptors, proprietary pharmaceutical data released for competition
challenges: Very high dimensionality (1776 features), feature interpretability limited due to proprietary nature, potential for overfitting
advantages: Real pharmaceutical industry data, large number of molecular descriptors, pre-normalized features
mathematical_background: Molecular descriptors capture 2D and 3D structural properties, physicochemical properties, and topological indices of molecules
research_impact: Demonstrates application of machine learning to drug discovery and molecular property prediction
ethical_considerations: Proprietary data with anonymized descriptors limits interpretability and reproducibility of chemical insights

original_source.creator: Boehringer Ingelheim (pharmaceutical company)
original_source.publication: Boehringer Ingelheim: Predicting a Biological Response
